<module>
    <h>sgìth</h>
    <p><g>sgìth</g>
        <en>tired</en> is a <a href="?xx=adjectives/simple_adjectives">simple adjective</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Like other (gradable) adjectives, <g>sgìth</g> can occur with an intensifying
                pre-specifier like <a href="?gd=glee"><g>glé</g></a>
                <en>very</en>.</p>
            <p>
                <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha mi <m>glé sgìth</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>I am very tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-predicate">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>sgìth</g> can be used (uninflected) as the predicate of the
                verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Màiri <m>sgìth</m>. Tha i <m>sgìth</m> ag obair anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary is tired. She is tired working in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha mi fuar agus tha mi <m>sgìth</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>I am cold and I am tired.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach eil thu <m>sgìth</m>?</gd>
                        <tr>Aren’t you tired?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
